Text: Synthetic Storage Liquidation VariancesForwarded by Dawn C KenneHOUECT on AM Dawn C Kenne PM To Darron C CT cc Subject Synthetic Storage Liquidation Variances Darron I am going to try to put my thoughts on paper but call me if there are any further questions For April we have of expense on the back page I have narrowed it down to the following Tagg N being double booked the correct tagg is N The other side of the storage transaction is in physical liquidation file and it is for Looks like double booking it actually made us money Check it out though in liquidations should have been moved to commodity expense to cover transportations OA but it wasnt so we this is income for us Two deals were booked in sitara but not tagg and therefore no liquidation to cover the expenses They are sitara and The total of these equaled For May we have in income on the back page This comes from Another deal booked twiceTagg N was booked as duplicate the right one is N The other side expense of the deal was taken in Dec Therefore I see this as true income Tagg NJ I will have to talk with you about this I dont fully understand it myself Tagg NG this should have been transferred to rd party salespurchases This storage deal is booked directly with the third party I have not looked at July in full but have some print outs to give you Please let me know if you have any further questions on this crap I am just a phone call away Dawn

FW Mapping Questar location and index Cc the pub codes to be mapped to the indexes that Steve South has requested listed below Thanks Dawn Original Message From Walker Chris Sent Tuesday April AM To Kenne Dawn C Sweitzer Tara Cc Meredith Kevin Lozano Melba Cass Robert B Subject Mapping Questar location and index Dawn and Tara Please map the following in TEST when you have the chance for Steve South location Questar Pipeline Company North System The transaction is for delivery at the Questar Pipeline Company North System index Questar GDD The Index for a day shall be the Daily Midpoint price published on such calendar day under the heading Daily Price Survey in the Rockies Questar section of Gas Daily or if a calendar day is not a Business Day then the price used shall be the Daily Midpoint price published on the next succeeding Business Day Questar IF NXL The Fixed Price shall be the settlement price for the last scheduled Trading Day of the NYMEX Henry Hub Natural Gas Futures Contract modified by the price submitted by the Counterparty on the Website for the applicable Determination Period The Index shall be the first price published during the applicable Determination Period by Inside Fercs Gas Market Report in the section Prices of Spot Gas Delivered to Pipelines under the heading Questar Pipeline Co Rocky Mountains Questar GDD IF The Fixed Price shall be the Questar Pipeline Co Rocky Mountains price as listed in the section entitled Prices of Spot Gas Delivered to Pipelines published in the first issue in such month of Inside Fercs Gas Market Report modified by the price submitted by the Counterparty on the Website for the applicable Determination Period The Index for a day shall be the Daily Midpoint price published on such calendar day under the heading Daily Price Survey in the Rockies Questar section of Gas Daily or if a calendar day is not a Business Day then the price used shall be the Daily Midpoint price published on the next succeeding Business Day Thanks CW

Option Logic Cc the tagg test environment is running I have tested the option logic with the new NGExotic book Please review the following deals in tagg stage and let me know if this is correct QQ Call Option QQ Hedge If this is the way it should be booked in tagg it is all contingent on Mike Maggi deleting the current option suites active on option manager recreating them and selecting NGExotic as the risk book under the auto hedge selection We will be more than happy to provide assistance if needed If you approve we will place this logic into production this evening after trading If this does not look correct or if you have any further questions please contact Dawn or Tara Thank you for your help Dawn

Cc This is what I spoke to you about on the phone In order to prepare for the new BrokerClient application that EOL will be supporting we need to clean up the EOL deals in tagg We have found alot of deals in tagg that have EOL in the broker field but no EOL deal number Most of these are due to second legs being added manually after the EOL transaction or the EOL deal number being deleted from the tagg leg We are asking risk to go thru these deals and add the EOL deal number to the legs that do not have the deal number listed For example if the deal is two legs and only one leg has the EOL number on it and clearly the other legs are associated with the one EOL transaction manually enter the EOL deal number into the remaining legs Attached is the list of deals I spot checked several of these and pretty much found the common trend of one leg has just EOL in the broker field and the second leg has EOL in the broker field and an EOL deal number I have seperated the list into different tabs by counterparty name Please let me know if you have any questions Thanks Dawn

Re EOL Broker Clean Up Cc Do you have time to sit down this afternoon or tomorrow morning to go over this issue Dawn Jeffrey C Gossett AM To Dawn C CT Torrey CT cc Errol NRON Subject Re EOL Broker Clean Up TorreyDawn Do you guys really think this is a reasonable reqeust Looks like there are in excess of deals If you guys need this field covered we need to come up with a better process than manually changing deals in TAGG Let me know how you would like to handle this or if we need to discuss further We will be happy to assist you any way we can short of manually going into deals Thanks Dawn C Kenne PM To Jeffrey C CT cc Tara CT Torrey CT Subject EOL Broker Clean Up Jeff I am attaching a list of EOL transactions that we need your help cleaning up With the new BrokerClient application that EOL is bringing on this weekend we need to remove EOL from the broker field What we have run into is there are many deals in Tagg that have EOL in the broker field but no EOL number We are requesting that risk go through and add the EOL deal number to the tagg legs where there is none listed The reason for this is that if we remove EOL from the broker field and there is no EOL deal number reference then there is no way to no if that deal is an EOL deal For audit purposes no one could tie back to the deals Please give this list to the appropriate risk groups by index Let me know if you have any further questions ALSO this list is in addition to the list that I provided Errol yesterday Thank you Dawn

gas daily options Cc George Please review QU in tagg stage and let me know if it looks alright Also this is going out Monday so please keep a close eye on these trades to make sure they are bridging correctly Thanks Dawn

duplicate deals Cc currently working on a situation where the bridge is creating duplicate deals This started yesterday and we contacted the appropriate books to kill the duplicate deal Yesterday there were a total of eight deals duplicating so far today there are six They have narrowed down the problem and Mike Swaim and Oscar Rivera think it should be resolved this afternoon Meanwhile Oscar is running a query that will let us know the duplicate deals He will run this throughout the day and I will email you the deals Listed below in Bold is the duplicate deals from today two are from late last night I have placed the risk book next to the deals Please forward this to the appropriate people in your group I was not sure who runs the Singapore book if London could let me know I would appreciate it I will keep you updated on the progress Sorry for any inconvenience this may be causing Feel free to call me if you would like more information Thanks Dawn Forwarded by Dawn C KenneHOUECT on AM From Oscar nronXgate on AM To Dawn C CT cc Subject duplicate deals Dawn This is the list of duplicate deals The last on the list are new TAGGDeal EOL Deal CREATEDDTM V AM V AM V AM V PM V PM V PM V PM V PM V PM Singapore V PM Singapore V AM East New York V AM GDailyEst V AM WTIGWNXC V AM GDailyEst

Counterparties w Master Agreements with ECC Cc the paragragh in red below from an email I sent last month I need risk to confirm that all counterparties that have master agreements with ECC now counterparties need to be booked with legs as described below in red We need this confirmation from risk as soon as possible We are pushing IT to get this logic in place and dont want anything to blow up for risk Please respond by email Thank you for your cooperation Dawn Forwarded by Dawn C KenneHOUECT on PM Dawn C Kenne AM To Jeffrey C CT Michael CT Torrey CT Tara CT cc Jennifer deBoisblanc CT Kam CT Darron C CT William CT David CT Subject Counterparties w Master Agreements with ECC I have received an updated list of the counterparties that have Master Agreements with ECC There are now about counterparties that fall under this category What seems to be happening is that these counterparties are hitting on US gas products on EOL and are not bridging into Tagg correctly Currently they are bridging as one leg between ENA and the counterparty The problem arises during settlement because ENA cannot settle with these counterparties only ECC can An example of what Risk is doing to the products after bridging is TaggQ EOL RISK We need risk to verify that anytime without exception all companies with Master Agreements with ECC that hit a US product must be booked as two legs leg one booked between ECC and the counterparty with risk assignment of FTUSCANDERMS leg two flipping the risk out of FTUSCANDERMS to the appropriate risk book Also risk needs to verify that this is only for Financial Swaps and not Physical deals IT It is my understanding that a few counterparties are set up to be booked correctly with two legs The list is now up to counterparties and will most likely be updated on a consistent basis Is this something that Tagg Maintenance can handle Guidelines need to be set up for RiskGlobal to instruct IT when new Master Agreements are created with counterparties so logic can be adjusted accordingly Does a meeting need to be set up to elaborate on these issues Are there any further issues that need to be addressed concerning ECC Master Agreements Please respond with your thoughts on this subject Thank you Dawn
